cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for interpreting and simplifying a black box model of a deep random forest, which is a machine learning model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance and generalizability of the model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of decision trees and feature contributions suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the mention of deep neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
